JOHANNESBURG - The Bafana Bafana squad to face Cape Verde in back-to-back 2018 FIFA World Cup qualifiers will be announced on Wednesday.South Africa takes on Cape Verde on Friday, 1 September, at the Estadio Nacional Stadium in Cape Verde which kicks off at 8.30pm (SA time).READ: Late Zambian volley forces draw with BafanaThe return leg will be played on Tuesday, 5 September at the Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban at 7pm.These will be Bafana Bafana s third and fourth match of the qualifiers.South Africa played to a 1-1 draw against Burkina Faso in Oaugadougou in October 2016 and followed it up with a 2-1 win over Senegal in Polokwane in November 2016.African News Agency